----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Revised spec to incorporate explicit streak state with count and multiplier
-- Summary 2: Added states for successive correct answers up to 3x multiplier and reset state
-- Summary 3: Defined state transition constraints based on acceptance criteria
-- Summary 4: Fixed type errors in predicates (channel kind comparisons)
-- Summary 5: Removed contradictory constraints (single vs redundant channels; kept single for performance)
-- Summary 6: Adjusted test case contracts to match actual streak progression
-- Summary 7: Model is now satisfiable and can verify reachability of all acceptance criteria
-- Assumption 1: Player role is represented as Actor Player with Read and Write permissions
-- Assumption 2: Permission lattice simplified to required permissions only
-- Assumption 3: Non-functional requirements are modelled as structural constraints (single channel, UI channel, actor initiation)
-- Assumption 4: Streak progression is linear up to 4 consecutive correct answers, then stays at 3x multiplier
-- Assumption 5: Incorrect answer from any streak state resets to Pre1-equivalent state (PostReset)
-- Open issue 1: Test case TC-ANS-02 expects 3x multiplier for third correct answer, but acceptance criteria specify 2x for third and 3x for fourth; spec follows acceptance criteria
-- Open issue 2: Resource and Permission signatures are retained for structural compatibility but are not central to streak behavior; may be simplified further
-- Open issue 3: Scalability constraint (every actor initiates) forces at least one operation per Actor, which may be too strong but is retained as placeholder


